<head>
 <title>CSS3 실습 예제</title>
<script>
    //2.
function res(){
 var a=document.getElementById("k1");
 var a2=eval(3+4);
 a.innerHTML=a2;
}
 function res2(){
 var b=document.getElementById("k2");
 var b2=eval(5+20+60);
 b.innerHTML=b2;
}
 function res3(){
 var c=document.getElementById("k3");
 var c2=eval(20/5-4*5);
 c.innerHTML=c2;
}
</script>
</head>
<body>
    <!--1.-->
    <h2>라면을 끓이는 순서</h2>
    <hr>
    <ol type='A' onclick="this.style.backgroundColor='yellow'">
        <li>물을 끓인다.</li>
        <li>라면과 스프를 넣는다.</li>
        <li>계란을 넣는다.</li>
        <li>얌얌맛있게 먹는다.</li>        
</ol>
<!--2.-->
<h2>계산해봅시다.</h2>
<hr>
<ul>
    <li>3 + 4 = <label onclick="res()" id="k1">답</label></li>
    <li>5 + 20 + 60 = <label onclick="res2()" id="k2">답</label></li>
    <li>20 / 5 - 4 * 5 = <label onclick="res3()" id="k3">답</label></li>
</ul>

</ul>
<script>
    //1.
     var n=document.getElementsByTagName("li");
     for(var i=0; i<4; i++){  //복수개니까 for문을 써준다
        var a=n[i];
        a.style.color='green';
      }

</script>


